 Corporate partnerships play a significant role in student development. Industry relationships help sustain a collaborative learning environment that promotes engagement with company representatives and exposure to real-world challenges and conditions for students. Corporate philanthropic support also strengthens AHS in its efforts to broaden understanding of applied health sciences and disability and to expand opportunities for its students.  The AHS Corporate Partners Program provides numerous opportunities for its corporate members, including:  Access to AHS leadership to advise, provide industry perspective, and impact curriculum development.  Recruit a targeted student demographic through early access to expanded recruiting opportunities.  Collaborate with students and faculty on sponsored research projects and other opportunities.  Reach thousands of AHS students, faculty and staff via targeted marketing and branding strategies.  Receive access to AHS faculty and facilities for corporate consultations, meetings and focus groups.            Corporate Partners Program Benefits Partner Associate Supporter      Membership to the AHS Dean’s Advisory Council ✓    Host an AHS Partners Day ✓    Submit one industry-sponsored student project ✓    Direct access to the college dean ✓ ✓    Access to AHS faculty ✓ ✓    Serve as an industry guest speaker ✓ ✓    Receive invitations to attend AHS events ✓ ✓ ✓    Sponsor an AHS event, competition or award ✓ ✓ ✓    Host AHS students in your facilities ✓ ✓ ✓    Access AHS facilities ✓ ✓ ✓    Acknowledgement in AHS Magazine ✓ ✓ ✓    Recognition on the AHS website ✓ ✓ ✓                  Contact Larry McCollum, director of corporate relations, to learn how your company can become an AHS Corporate Partner Program member.    You can contact Larry at:     Email  lmccoll@uic.edu      Phone  (312) 413-8891      Address  601 S. Morgan St. 2510 UH (MC 002) Chicago, IL 60607               AHS Alumni    Back to main content           Give to